# Figma MCP — Afenda Design System Rules

Use when implementing designs from Figma MCP (`get_design_context`, `get_screenshot`) into this monorepo.

**Auth Figma file:** `https://www.figma.com/design/2ZNqNOxyNb5TwCTBIaMVPD/loginauth`  
**File key:** `2ZNqNOxyNb5TwCTBIaMVPD`

## 1. Token definitions

| Layer | Authority | CSS prefix |
|-------|-----------|------------|
| Afenda raw + extensions (PAS-005 SSOT) | `packages/css-authority/src/authorities/afenda-extensions.json` · runtime `packages/css-authority/src/css/afenda-tokens.css` | `--afenda-*` |
| shadcn bridge + `@theme` | `packages/css-authority/src/css/afenda-runtime-bridge.css` · vendored `packages/css-authority/src/css/vendored/shadcn-theme.css` | `--background`, `--primary`, `--border`, … |
| App shell | `packages/appshell/src/styles/afenda-appshell.css` | `--app-shell-*` |
| Auth editorial | `packages/css-authority/src/authorities/auth-editorial.json` | `--auth-editorial-*` |
| Studio blocks | `packages/appshell/src/styles/afenda-appshell-studio.css` §A | `--app-shell-studio-*` |

**Add CSS tokens:** authority JSON under `packages/css-authority/src/authorities/` → `pnpm --filter @afenda/css-authority generate:css-authority-registry` — not `packages/ui` `token.registry.ts` (Governed UI TS only).

**Figma → code:** Map Figma variables via `get_variable_defs` to `--afenda-semantic-*` / shadcn bridge vars — never invent hex in components.

## 2. Component library

| Consumer | Import | Rule |
|----------|--------|------|
| Primitives | `@afenda/ui` | `intent`, `emphasis`, `size`, `presentation` — **no `className`** |
| Governance | `@afenda/ui/governance` | Types only |
| Auth shell | `@afenda/appshell/auth-shell` | `AuthShellEntry`, `AuthShellEntryBrand`, `AuthShellError` |
| App forms | `AuthForm` compound | `apps/erp/src/app/(auth)/_components/auth-form.compound.tsx` |

Install missing primitives: `npx shadcn@latest add <name> -c packages/ui`

## 3. Frameworks

- React 19 + Next.js App Router (`apps/erp`)
- Tailwind v4 via `globals.css` — **not** for auth shell chrome
- Auth shell chrome: BEM in `packages/appshell/src/auth-shell/auth-shell.css` (`.af-auth-shell*`) and `afenda-appshell-studio.css` §L where studio patterns apply

## 4. Assets

| Asset | Path |
|-------|------|
| Brand artifact (hero) | `apps/erp/public/auth/auth-brand-artifact.jpg` (preferred) or `auth-entry-preview.png` fallback |
| Figma MCP exports | `download_assets` → save under `apps/erp/public/auth/` |
| Images in shell | `AppShellOptimizedImage` / `AuthShellBrandArtifactImage` |

`apps/erp/next.config.ts` allows `localhost:3845` for Figma Desktop MCP image URLs.

## 5. Icons

- `lucide-react` only in auth-shell
- Capability map: `auth-shell-brand.compound.tsx` — `aria-hidden` on decorative icons

## 6. Styling approach

```
apps/erp/globals.css
  → @afenda/ui/afenda-ui.css
  → @afenda/appshell/afenda-appshell.css
  → apps/erp/(auth)/auth.css   ← form rhythm only
```

**Never** import `afenda-appshell-studio.css` from apps. After shell CSS edits: `pnpm sync:package-css-dist -- --package @afenda/appshell`

## 7. Auth promotion pipeline

Figma output is **reference only**. Promote through:

1. `packages/appshell/src/auth-shell/` — layout compounds + contract copy
2. `afenda-appshell-studio.css` §L — visual patterns (image-led brand, cardless form)
3. `apps/erp/(auth)/` — forms, copy registry, `auth.css`

## 8. Image-led auth (brand panel)

- **Mode:** artifact-led — full-bleed photograph/scene, not floating UI card
- **Text:** anchored on scrim; brand kicker loudest
- **Form column:** utility copy, cardless (frontend-skill Apps)
- **Reject:** 3D tilt, beam animations, glass pill soup, dashboard-in-a-card

## 9. Figma MCP workflow

1. `get_metadata` — list pages/frames (`fileKey: 2ZNqNOxyNb5TwCTBIaMVPD`)
2. `get_design_context` — per frame `nodeId` (convert `1-2` → `1:2`)
3. `get_variable_defs` — token alignment
4. Adapt to governed React + BEM — do not paste raw Tailwind output

## 10. Gates

```bash
pnpm sync:package-css-dist -- --package @afenda/appshell
pnpm --filter @afenda/appshell test auth-shell
pnpm --filter @afenda/erp exec vitest run "src/app/(auth)"
pnpm ui:guard:scan
```
